Method Detail

startInstance

ITaskInstance startInstance()
Starts a new instance of the corresponding TaskClass. The new instance will be a child task of the starting task. If the starting task will finish, the child task will be terminated by the system.

Returns:
The TaskInstance identifier.

startRootInstance

ITaskInstance startRootInstance()
Starts a new instance of the corresponding TaskClass. The new instance is started as new root instance. A root instance does not depend on the status or lifecycle of other tasks.

Returns:
The TaskInstance identifier.
